1
00:00:17,375 --> 00:00:19,750
[AKANE]
Yeah? Yeah. [giggles]

2
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,000
Oh, okay.

3
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:23,250
You know, I've always
wanted to go there, too.

4
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:27,375
And after that,
I was thinking-- Yeah.

5
00:00:27,458 --> 00:00:29,458
Is that okay? You sure?

6
00:00:29,541 --> 00:00:33,208
What?! Oh, come on.
Don't worry about that.

7
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:35,416
Just a little. Yeah.

8
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,208
[MASHIRO] Thanks to all
those businesses that have

9
00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:11,208
strong connections
with the Academy,

10
00:02:11,291 --> 00:02:13,000
and to all the alumni
and the efforts

11
00:02:13,083 --> 00:02:16,208
of various local businesses,
we are able to once again

12
00:02:16,291 --> 00:02:19,125
bring to you the
Founders' Day Festival.

13
00:02:19,208 --> 00:02:20,833
We hope that all
of you will enjoy...

14
00:02:20,916 --> 00:02:22,125
C'mon! Let's go, Kazu!

15
00:02:22,208 --> 00:02:23,250
[KAZUYA chuckles]

16
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:27,041
[MIKOTO]
Oh.

17
00:02:27,125 --> 00:02:28,875
[AOI] Where do you
wanna go first, Mikoto?

18
00:02:28,958 --> 00:02:29,875
[MIKOTO]
Hmm?

19
00:02:29,958 --> 00:02:31,291
Glad you asked!
First, I wanna--!

20
00:02:31,375 --> 00:02:32,791
--[CHIE, AOI] Huh?
--[MIKOTO whines]

21
00:02:32,875 --> 00:02:34,458
What's the matter,
spoiled little girl?

22
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:36,541
Feel a little lonely
without Mai?

23
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:39,666
No, I'm totally fine
without her!

24
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:42,583
Takumi...

25
00:02:42,666 --> 00:02:44,166
Yeah, Sister...?

26
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:48,291
[MAI sighs]

27
00:02:48,375 --> 00:02:50,666
Hmm. That's 36.8 degrees.

28
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:52,250
A perfectly normal temperature.

29
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:54,125
I keep telling ya
that I feel all right!

30
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:56,041
Just go to the
festival without me!

31
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:58,000
Mikoto's waiting for you, right?

32
00:02:58,083 --> 00:02:59,083
Don't worry.

33
00:02:59,166 --> 00:03:00,625
I've asked Chie and Aoi
to watch her.

34
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:01,916
Mai, c'mon!

35
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,583
[groans]
Enough.

36
00:03:03,666 --> 00:03:04,750
[TAKUMI]
Hmm...

37
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:07,500
You're sweating a bit, Takumi.

38
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:08,125
C'mere!

39
00:03:08,208 --> 00:03:09,291
Ah!

40
00:03:09,375 --> 00:03:11,458
--Knock it off! Get-- Ah!
--[AKIRA] Hmm...

41
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:12,583
[TAKUMI]
Stop it!

42
00:03:12,666 --> 00:03:14,541
[MAI giggles]
I won't stop!

43
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:17,250
Resistance is futile!
Now sit still!

44
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:18,333
[AKIRA grunts]

45
00:03:19,125 --> 00:03:20,583
Halt, intruder!

46
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:24,125
Let me change your shirt...

47
00:03:24,208 --> 00:03:26,333
Gimme a break. I thought
some girl had snuck in

48
00:03:26,416 --> 00:03:27,666
and was attacking him.

49
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:30,041
There's something definitely
weird about you two.

50
00:03:30,125 --> 00:03:31,375
[MAI chuckles]

51
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:33,500
Look, my fever's down,
so I'll be able to get out

52
00:03:33,583 --> 00:03:35,625
of the room soon,
Operations Officer.

53
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:37,250
I don't need your help!

54
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:39,083
Why don't you just let
your sister baby you?

55
00:03:39,166 --> 00:03:40,750
That's what you want, isn't it?

56
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:42,791
Ah! Akira!

57
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:43,791
[CHIE]
Ah!

58
00:03:43,875 --> 00:03:45,500
It looks pretty good.

59
00:03:45,583 --> 00:03:47,375
Oh! What's that over there?

60
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:49,541
It's a ramen noodle shop.

61
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:51,333
Ramen?! Ah!

62
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:53,458
[PROPRIETOR A]
One order of ramen soup!

63
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:54,625
Ah!

64
00:03:54,708 --> 00:03:56,166
[laughs]

65
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:03,291
[yelps]

66
00:04:03,375 --> 00:04:04,791
[shrieks]

67
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,708
[AOI, CHIE]
Hmm?

68
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:09,833
Whaddaya mean you don't
have enough tables?!

69
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:12,666
Okay. I hear ya.
I'll try to do something.

70
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:15,166
You're doing well.
I'm impressed, Tate.

71
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:17,500
How do you end up with
so much slack time?

72
00:04:17,583 --> 00:04:19,875
I was busy getting ready
up till yesterday.

73
00:04:19,958 --> 00:04:20,833
Trust me.

74
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:21,833
[groans]

75
00:04:21,916 --> 00:04:23,000
[REITO]
Hmph.

76
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:24,541
[SHIHO grunts]
I am mad!

77
00:04:24,625 --> 00:04:26,833
I was supposed to go around
the festival with my brother,

78
00:04:26,916 --> 00:04:29,166
but no! He's such a... 

79
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:30,666
...stupid jerk! Idiot! Brother!

80
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,625
For the finish!

81
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:34,708
[MIKOTO screams]

82
00:04:42,166 --> 00:04:44,041
[AKANE laughs]
Come on! Hurry!

83
00:04:44,125 --> 00:04:46,000
Hang on, Akane.

84
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:47,208
Hmm?

85
00:04:47,291 --> 00:04:48,125
[MAN A]
Come on.

86
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:51,083
Let's go. Just the two of us.

87
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,833
We should at least check it out.

88
00:04:53,916 --> 00:04:57,125
I mean, we haven't decided where
we're going for our summer trip.

89
00:04:57,208 --> 00:04:58,250
[gasps]

90
00:05:02,416 --> 00:05:03,750
[AKANE]
Jeez, Kazu.

91
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:05,958
You were thinking of something
perverted, weren't you?

92
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:07,375
[KAZUYA]
No!

93
00:05:07,458 --> 00:05:08,458
Honest!

94
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,416
[AKANE]
Let's come back later.

95
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,500
Huh?

96
00:05:13,583 --> 00:05:14,833
There's still tons of
other stuff here

97
00:05:14,916 --> 00:05:16,125
that I wanna see with you.

98
00:05:16,208 --> 00:05:17,333
[giggles]

99
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:18,458
[KAZUYA chuckles]

100
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:21,250
[MIKOTO screams]

101
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:23,625
[GREER] The Lord put forth
unto them, saying,

102
00:05:23,708 --> 00:05:27,875
"The Kingdom of Heaven is like
to a grain of a mustard seed..

103
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:29,833
Which a man took...

104
00:05:29,916 --> 00:05:31,916
Miyu, this is a rare chance.

105
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,333
You should go and see
what it's all about.

106
00:05:34,416 --> 00:05:36,791
I'll tell your father--
I mean, the Father,

107
00:05:36,875 --> 00:05:39,041
where you've gone, don't worry.

108
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:40,083
Okay.

109
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:41,875
[ISHIGAMI]
Please, let me help you

110
00:05:41,958 --> 00:05:44,208
with whatever you need,
Sister Yukariko.

111
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:46,250
Mr. Ishigami.

112
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:49,041
Did you, uh, think about
what I said, Sister?

113
00:05:49,125 --> 00:05:50,583
Oh, please stop.

114
00:05:50,666 --> 00:05:53,458
I couldn't possibly model
for your painting.

115
00:05:53,541 --> 00:05:54,291
Oh! Oh!

116
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:56,333
[MIKOTO whimpers]

117
00:05:56,416 --> 00:05:58,041
[YUKARIKO gasps, screams]

118
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:01,916
[AKANE, KAZUYA laugh]

119
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,125
[KAZUYA]
Yeah, right.

120
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:06,583
I'd heard this school
had a lot of money

121
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:09,708
to throw around and everything,
but this is incredible.

122
00:06:09,791 --> 00:06:13,458
[TAKUMI] Hmm. I feel
like we're outta place.

123
00:06:13,541 --> 00:06:14,708
[KAZUYA sighs]

124
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:17,041
Akane, you seem to be
really excited today.

125
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:19,625
I decided that I'm gonna have
as much fun as I can here!

126
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:20,875
I can help there.

127
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:23,541
So, where do you
wanna go next?

128
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:24,666
[AKANE sighs]

129
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:31,250
[AKANE]
Hmm...

130
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:32,083
[MAI]
Akane?

131
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:33,166
Ah?

132
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:34,833
Mai!

133
00:06:34,916 --> 00:06:36,791
[MAI]
Hi!

134
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:40,250
Guess what? I made up
my mind for sure this time.

135
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:41,958
Thanks for your advice.

136
00:06:42,041 --> 00:06:43,166
I really appreciate it.

137
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:44,250
My advice?

138
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:46,291
[AKANE giggles]
Yup! Anyway, that's all!

139
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:47,416
See ya!

140
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,958
[MAI]
Uh...

141
00:06:50,041 --> 00:06:51,500
[YUICHI]
Sorry to make you help out.

142
00:06:51,583 --> 00:06:52,541
[REITO]
That's okay.

143
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:53,875
There should be
some spare tables

144
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:55,375
in the basement of the library.

145
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:56,750
Let's hurry.

146
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:57,875
Ah.

147
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:00,041
[BOTH]
Huh?

148
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:02,333
[ANNOUNCER]
A real haunted house!

149
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:04,291
Think you have the
courage to come in...?

150
00:07:04,375 --> 00:07:05,750
--[laughs maniacally]
--[HARUKA snarls]

151
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:08,208
It's not nearly scary enough...

152
00:07:08,291 --> 00:07:09,166
Yukino!

153
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:11,458
What is it this time, Haruka?

154
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:12,833
[HARUKA gasps]
A ghost!

155
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:15,166
That's not very nice, Haruka.

156
00:07:15,250 --> 00:07:16,416
--[GIRL A shrieks]
--[BOTH] Huh?

157
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:17,791
[STUDENTS screaming]

158
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:18,875
[MIKOTO wails]

159
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:19,791
Wha--?

160
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:20,916
[MIKOTO wails]

161
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,791
[BOTH gasp]

162
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,500
I can't stand these
school festivals.

163
00:07:24,583 --> 00:07:25,833
They don't do anything for me.

164
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:27,041
--[crashing]
--[MIKOTO squeals]

165
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:28,791
[NATSUKI]
Hmm?

166
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:30,291
[BOTH cough]

167
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:31,833
[MIKOTO whimpers]

168
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:34,541
[wails]

169
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:35,458
[NATSUKI]
Hmm.

170
00:07:35,541 --> 00:07:37,541
Water...

171
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:40,416
[BUSINESSMAN A] So, if it's
not too forward of me,

172
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:43,333
I was wondering if we could
speak regarding your purchases

173
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:45,000
of our products for next year.

174
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:48,833
Oh, please.
Sir, his is a tea ceremony.

175
00:07:48,916 --> 00:07:51,500
We can talk about
business matters later.

176
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:53,583
The thing is, we're
a little pressed for--

177
00:07:53,666 --> 00:07:55,375
[SHIZURU]
The headmaster of the academy

178
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:58,041
has given me the
necessary authority.

179
00:07:58,125 --> 00:08:01,666
So we can have
a nice, long talk later.

180
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,541
Right?

181
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,458
Uh... All right...

182
00:08:08,291 --> 00:08:09,541
[sighs]

183
00:08:09,625 --> 00:08:12,291
[FUMI]
Are you tired?

184
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:13,500
Terrible, huh?

185
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:15,750
It was only a little
public appearance, too.

186
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:18,500
This is no good at all,
leaving Miss Fujino

187
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:20,958
to deal with all
the important people.

188
00:08:21,041 --> 00:08:22,916
[FUMI]
You mustn't say that.

189
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,000
What you need now is rest.

190
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:26,375
[MASHIRO]
I know, but...

191
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:30,083
Please don't make it
difficult for me, Miss Mashiro.

192
00:08:34,416 --> 00:08:36,625
[REITO] Sorry to make
you guys help out like this.

193
00:08:36,708 --> 00:08:38,708
No problem.
It's not out of our way.

194
00:08:38,791 --> 00:08:40,375
And she's got the muscles.

195
00:08:40,458 --> 00:08:42,291
Uh, I heard that!

196
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:44,333
[YUICHI]
Ack! Found a spider web!

197
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:46,875
Ugh! No way!
There's spiders in here?!

198
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:48,666
Yeah. There's one on your back.

199
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:52,416
[MAI]
Hmm? [squeals]

200
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,958
[whimpers]

201
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:57,291
[gulps] Jeez, don't you even
know a joke when you hear one?

202
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,791
[MAI growls]

203
00:08:58,875 --> 00:08:59,666
Jerk!

204
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,583
Ah! Sorry! Honest!

205
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:03,541
You sure don't sound sorry!

206
00:09:03,625 --> 00:09:05,375
[grunts, growls]

207
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:06,250
You stupid--!

208
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:07,125
[YUICHI]
Stop it!

209
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,041
[MAI growls]

210
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:09,541
[gasps]

211
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:10,958
No way...

212
00:09:11,041 --> 00:09:13,250
[screams]

213
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:14,000
Tokiha!

214
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:14,791
Mai!

215
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,250
Sis! You okay?!

216
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:17,333
[screaming]

217
00:09:19,708 --> 00:09:22,958
Well, she sure is cute
as she is troublesome.

218
00:09:23,041 --> 00:09:25,791
Still, we should settle
this once and for all,

219
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:26,875
Mai...

220
00:09:30,958 --> 00:09:32,791
[MAI groans]

221
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:35,000
[REITO] Sorry, but
if you wouldn't mind...

222
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:37,708
I'd appreciate it if
you got off my back.

223
00:09:37,791 --> 00:09:40,166
[MAI]
Hmm--? Sorry!

224
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:42,166
Where are we...?

225
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:43,750
Takumi!

226
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,000
Takumi?!

227
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,791
Can you hear me, Sis?!

228
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:50,833
Kanzaki! Hey!

229
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:53,833
The cell phone
doesn't work either?

230
00:09:53,916 --> 00:09:55,000
This isn't happening.

231
00:09:55,083 --> 00:09:56,833
Mikoto!

232
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:58,875
Typical. Where did she get to?

233
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:01,041
She's such a wild cat!

234
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:02,250
Oh.

235
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:04,333
[MIKOTO grunting]
Some of those, too!

236
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:05,916
[growls]
Now cut it out!

237
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:09,541
That's enough food and more than
enough of your crazy rampage!

238
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:11,583
Hey, message for the
owner of this animal!

239
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:14,500
Please train her properly,
and either put her on a leash

240
00:10:14,583 --> 00:10:16,166
or stick her in a cage!

241
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,250
[growls]

242
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:19,125
[STAGE MC]
Next on the program today,

243
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:20,958
we present to you
music from the choir

244
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:22,916
led by the pride of our
academy,

245
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,041
the "Golden Angel"
Alyssa Searrs,

246
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,916
who is currently in
elementary school...

247
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,958
[KAZUYA] Wow. I had
no idea this place existed.

248
00:10:31,041 --> 00:10:33,208
Listen, Kazu...

249
00:10:33,291 --> 00:10:35,541
When we decided
to go out together,

250
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:39,208
we agreed that we wouldn't hide
anything from each other, right?

251
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:41,583
Uh-huh.

252
00:10:41,666 --> 00:10:43,750
[AKANE] Well, there's
something I've been wanting

253
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:45,208
to talk to you about.

254
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:48,000
[AKANE whimpers]

255
00:10:48,083 --> 00:10:49,083
[gasps]

256
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:04,500
[MAI] This is under
the school, isn't it?

257
00:11:04,583 --> 00:11:06,916
[REITO]
Yeah, at least I think so.

258
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,583
What's with
this school, anyway?!

259
00:11:09,666 --> 00:11:13,916
Ugh! I'm getting angrier
and angrier every second!

260
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:17,041
That stupid Tate is to blame
for getting us into this mess!

261
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:19,833
I'll make sure he pays
for this, big time!

262
00:11:19,916 --> 00:11:21,791
Now, now.

263
00:11:21,875 --> 00:11:25,291
I'm sure he only meant it
as a harmless prank.

264
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:27,291
[MAI groans]

265
00:11:27,375 --> 00:11:28,541
Hey, Mai.

266
00:11:28,625 --> 00:11:30,375
Can I ask something personal?

267
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:31,583
[gasps]

268
00:11:31,666 --> 00:11:33,916
[REITO]
Do you have a... thing for Tate?

269
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,416
What?! [groans]

270
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,375
Why would you ask that
all of a sudden?!

271
00:11:38,458 --> 00:11:42,416
I don't feel anything for him!
Nothing at all! Ugh...

272
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,000
[laughs]

273
00:11:44,083 --> 00:11:46,125
Besides, there's that
promise I made to Shiho...

274
00:11:46,208 --> 00:11:48,833
Then does that mean that
I have a chance with you?

275
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:49,541
[gasps]

276
00:11:49,625 --> 00:11:51,666
Ah!

277
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:55,208
[YUICHI sighs]
I sure screwed up this one...

278
00:11:55,291 --> 00:11:56,500
I shouldn't have tempted fate

279
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:59,583
with that stupid spider prank
on your sister.

280
00:11:59,666 --> 00:12:01,625
Yeah, Mai's always
hated spiders,

281
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,750
for as long as I can
remember, actually.

282
00:12:05,958 --> 00:12:08,416
She tries to put on
such a tough act,

283
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:12,875
but I guess, after all, she is
just a regular high school girl.

284
00:12:12,958 --> 00:12:13,875
Yuichi...

285
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:15,208
I was wondering...

286
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,583
I know I asked you before
if you liked my sister.

287
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:19,291
That hasn't changed, has it?

288
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,625
Don't worry.

289
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:23,916
I won't steal your sister
away from you, Takumi.

290
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,333
I mean, I realize
that it's wrong...

291
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:28,375
It's wrong to be like this...

292
00:12:28,458 --> 00:12:29,833
But... it's...

293
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:31,125
[gasps]

294
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,208
Huh?

295
00:12:38,083 --> 00:12:38,958
No way!

296
00:12:39,041 --> 00:12:40,041
What the--

297
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:50,083
Uh...

298
00:12:50,166 --> 00:12:51,666
--[grass rustling]
--[gasps]

299
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:52,833
Miyu!

300
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,916
[MIYU]
Help me, Akane!

301
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
It's that monster from before!

302
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:00,041
[gasps]

303
00:13:00,125 --> 00:13:01,333
Holy...

304
00:13:05,958 --> 00:13:07,750
Let's get outta here!
Can you run?!

305
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:08,875
Uh, yeah!

306
00:13:13,458 --> 00:13:15,000
[pants]

307
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:16,125
Takumi!

308
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,541
[AKANE]
Kazuya...

309
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:25,541
Please...

310
00:13:25,625 --> 00:13:27,041
Don't hate me...

311
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:28,250
[KAZUYA gasps]

312
00:13:33,416 --> 00:13:37,583
[ALYSSA] ♪ Who are those
little girls in pain? ♪

313
00:13:37,666 --> 00:13:42,750
♪ Just trapped in castle
of dark side moon. ♪

314
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:47,208
♪ Twelve of them shining
bright in vain, ♪

315
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:50,000
♪ Like flowers that
blossom just once... ♪

316
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:51,541
[AKANE]
I was afraid.

317
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:53,750
I was afraid for so long...

318
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:57,583
Ever since Miyu saw me that
day at the bus accident...

319
00:13:57,666 --> 00:14:01,250
[ALYSSA] ♪ ...of a place
where they're free as dove. ♪

320
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:04,916
I was worried. I knew
you'd find out one day...

321
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,083
Kazu...

322
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:09,125
[panting]

323
00:14:09,208 --> 00:14:10,291
Damn it!

324
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:16,875
[BOTH grunt, gasp]

325
00:14:18,416 --> 00:14:19,875
--Wha--?!
--[gasps]

326
00:14:21,625 --> 00:14:22,416
Takumi!

327
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,250
Tate!

328
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:24,333
[gasps]

329
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:27,208
Go, Mai! Hurry!

330
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:28,250
Get out of here!

331
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:29,375
Huh?!

332
00:14:33,041 --> 00:14:35,166
[ALYSSA] ♪ They're
dancing in the shadow ♪

333
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,958
--like whispers of love. ♪
--Mai!

334
00:14:37,041 --> 00:14:39,708
[AKANE]
At first, I wondered, why me?

335
00:14:39,791 --> 00:14:42,250
I heard that the fate of
the world depended on it,

336
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,791
and I thought,
"How how was that possible?"

337
00:14:44,875 --> 00:14:47,125
But now, I've made up my mind.

338
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:48,208
I'll do it.

339
00:14:48,291 --> 00:14:49,333
For you.

340
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:52,250
Hari!

341
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:58,916
[MAI growls]

342
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:03,625
[REITO gasps]

343
00:15:07,416 --> 00:15:08,666
Kagutsuchi!

344
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:23,875
[REITO gasps]

345
00:15:23,958 --> 00:15:25,041
[KAZUYA gasps]

346
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:28,000
[yells]

347
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:29,125
[screams]

348
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:43,916
Kagutsuchi!

349
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:51,166
Hari!

350
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:08,125
[MAI grunts]

351
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:11,916
[NAGI]
Whoa... Well, well...

352
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,208
Oh-- What's that?

353
00:16:13,291 --> 00:16:14,541
An earthquake?

354
00:16:15,625 --> 00:16:17,000
[YUKINO whimpers]

355
00:16:17,083 --> 00:16:18,791
I'm scared...

356
00:16:25,291 --> 00:16:26,666
I'm sorry.

357
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:29,583
I guess I'd forgotten...

358
00:16:29,666 --> 00:16:32,583
Forgotten why I accepted you...

359
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:33,791
Now I remember.

360
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:36,458
It was to protect
the most precious thing.

361
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,041
[MAI sighs]

362
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:43,250
What's going on?

363
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:45,583
I'm sorry...

364
00:16:45,666 --> 00:16:47,750
Please don't ask me anything.

365
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:49,416
Not now, at least.

366
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:50,500
[REITO]
Huh.

367
00:16:55,375 --> 00:16:58,000
[YUICHI groans]

368
00:16:58,083 --> 00:17:00,916
Kanzaki...? Is that you...?

369
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,708
Why are you here?
What happened to that monster?!

370
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:07,708
Wish I could answer that.
I don't know myself, really.

371
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:11,750
[groans]
It's you, Sis...

372
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:13,375
Thank goodness.

373
00:17:13,458 --> 00:17:14,541
[sighs]

374
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:16,208
Takumi...!

375
00:17:23,666 --> 00:17:25,625
Akane...

376
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:28,291
[AKANE] You probably
don't like me anymore.

377
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:31,083
You're afraid of me
like this, right?

378
00:17:31,166 --> 00:17:32,166
[sniffs]

379
00:17:41,041 --> 00:17:42,541
[KAZUYA] You think
I'm gonna stop loving you

380
00:17:42,625 --> 00:17:44,416
over something like this?

381
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:47,625
Not likely.

382
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:49,166
Oh, Kazu...

383
00:17:53,291 --> 00:17:57,125
[AKANE sobs]

384
00:17:57,208 --> 00:17:58,833
I love you...

385
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:10,541
[inaudible]

386
00:18:14,625 --> 00:18:17,333
[AKANE]
Thank you, Miyu.

387
00:18:17,416 --> 00:18:20,291
You kept quiet about
what you saw, but I...

388
00:18:20,375 --> 00:18:24,083
[MIYU] I'm the one who
should be thanking you.

389
00:18:24,166 --> 00:18:27,166
I was able to gather
some very valuable data.

390
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,750
Huh...?

391
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,291
Miyu? Uh...

392
00:18:31,375 --> 00:18:32,708
But there is something else.

393
00:18:32,791 --> 00:18:35,500
I need to test one last thing
before I'm done here.

394
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:37,666
[HARI growls]

395
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:38,791
[AKANE gasps]

396
00:18:40,125 --> 00:18:45,125
[beeping, drives whirring]

397
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:04,666
[roars]

398
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:09,125
[gasps]

399
00:19:09,208 --> 00:19:12,208
[shrieks]

400
00:19:12,291 --> 00:19:13,291
[gasps]

401
00:19:14,666 --> 00:19:17,916
And now, Mai should fall
in line with my plans.

402
00:19:18,708 --> 00:19:19,625
[chime tolls]

403
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:20,750
[gasps]

404
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:33,291
[AKANE whimpers]

405
00:19:33,375 --> 00:19:34,500
Akane!

406
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:37,708
Goodbye, Akane.

407
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:40,375
I'm going to die...

408
00:19:40,458 --> 00:19:42,291
That's what'll happen...

409
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:43,916
[KAZUYA yelps]

410
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,166
--[groaning]
--[AKANE] Kazu?

411
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:48,000
--[groans, gasps]
--[AKANE gasps]

412
00:19:48,083 --> 00:19:49,125
Kazu!

413
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:52,416
[whimpers]

414
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:54,708
Help me... Akane...

415
00:19:54,791 --> 00:19:56,583
[AKANE gasps]

416
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:58,250
I... Ah...

417
00:19:59,750 --> 00:20:01,125
[sighs]

418
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:09,916
[AKANE]
This can't be.

419
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,083
This isn't happening.

420
00:20:12,166 --> 00:20:13,625
Kazu?

421
00:20:13,708 --> 00:20:15,416
Open your eyes.

422
00:20:21,625 --> 00:20:22,958
[AKANE]
No...

423
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:24,041
No...

424
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,541
[AKANE]
No, Kazu...

425
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:30,000
[gasps, wails]

426
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:34,166
[pants shrilly, screams]

427
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:35,791
Impossible!

428
00:20:35,875 --> 00:20:37,375
How could this happen?

429
00:20:39,208 --> 00:20:40,583
[AKANE]
Kazu...

430
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:45,500
I told you,
right at the beginning.

431
00:20:45,583 --> 00:20:48,791
That you'd be putting the thing
most precious to you at stake.

432
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,416
Kazu...

433
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,833
Come back...

434
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:55,000
Now you know.

435
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:57,708
It wasn't about
your own life, Akane.

436
00:20:57,791 --> 00:20:59,708
But rather...

437
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:02,541
It was the life of the person
you care about the most.

438
00:21:04,041 --> 00:21:05,333
[YUICHI]
Wow!

439
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:07,166
It leads to this place?

440
00:21:08,958 --> 00:21:12,375
Man... I guess the
festival's long done by now.

441
00:21:12,458 --> 00:21:14,541
That just leaves
the night festivities.

442
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:17,916
[YUICHI]
To think that the original plan

443
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,500
was to hold it on a boat.

444
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:24,041
I dunno, Mai.

445
00:21:24,125 --> 00:21:26,208
Hanging with you makes me
feel like I don't have

446
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:28,250
nearly enough lives to live.

447
00:21:29,375 --> 00:21:30,500
Sorry, Tate...

448
00:21:30,583 --> 00:21:32,416
Really...

449
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,458
[gasps]

450
00:21:33,541 --> 00:21:36,000
[TAKUMI]
Whoa!

451
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:38,291
Hey, did you say something?

452
00:21:38,375 --> 00:21:40,208
[fireworks booming]

453
00:21:40,291 --> 00:21:42,166
You wish I said something.

454
00:21:42,250 --> 00:21:43,458
[YUICHI]
Hmm.

455
00:22:17,166 --> 00:22:19,958
[NAGI] I told you,
right at the beginning.

456
00:22:20,041 --> 00:22:23,291
That you'd be putting the thing
most precious to you at stake.

457
00:23:56,708 --> 00:23:59,750
[MIKOTO]
Hey, what's important to girls?

458
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:02,666
Something you lose at
the beach in the summer.

459
00:24:02,750 --> 00:24:04,000
[MAI]
That would be your wallet!

460
00:24:04,083 --> 00:24:05,083
It's easy to lose when

461
00:24:05,166 --> 00:24:06,500
you're wearing a
bathing suit, after all!

462
00:24:06,583 --> 00:24:07,583
[laughs]

463
00:24:07,666 --> 00:24:09,416
I figured the
answer was-- [censored]

464
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:10,666
[MAI]
Hey!

